03:46.041 --> 03:48.041
Because they literally--
They met,

03:48.125 --> 03:50.083
and they describe
the moment they met,

03:50.166 --> 03:51.541
and it was such a moment.

03:53.041 --> 03:55.291
Russo:
<i>It was the Presidents Weekend</i>

03:55.375 --> 03:58.166
<i>in February 1979,</i>

03:58.250 --> 04:02.291
and rather than hang around
New York for this long weekend,

04:02.375 --> 04:05.166
<i>I thought I'll go up</i>
<i>and visit a friend in Boston.</i>

04:07.750 --> 04:10.333
(street noise)

04:10.416 --> 04:13.000
Robin:
<i>And I was living in Boston,</i>

04:13.083 --> 04:15.500
<i>and I wanted to move,</i>
<i>and a friend said,</i>

04:15.583 --> 04:17.291
"Oh, there's this...

04:17.375 --> 04:19.583
<i>cool apartment.</i>
<i>You might like it there."</i>

04:21.458 --> 04:24.041
<i>I went upstairs.</i>
<i>It was like the third floor,</i>

04:24.125 --> 04:28.166
<i>-and I knocked on</i>
<i>this apartment door...</i>
-(knocking)

04:28.250 --> 04:30.166
and this voice said, "Come in."

04:30.250 --> 04:31.916
And I walked into this kitchen,

04:32.000 --> 04:33.875
<i>and sitting at</i>
<i>the kitchen table</i>

04:33.958 --> 04:36.916
<i>was Russo,</i>
<i>and no one else was there.</i>

04:37.000 --> 04:38.708
And it was like, who's this?

04:38.791 --> 04:39.791
♪ ♪

04:39.875 --> 04:42.291
It was immediate.
Like a bomb!

04:42.375 --> 04:44.291
Kaboom. It was a thunderbolt.
It was like...

04:44.375 --> 04:45.958
I don't even know
what it was.

04:46.041 --> 04:49.541
<i>♪ Like a ball of lightning</i>
<i>and a ball of...♪</i>

04:49.625 --> 04:51.541
So we spent, like, an hour

04:51.625 --> 04:54.250
in the kitchen,
just the two of us together.

04:54.333 --> 04:55.791
<i>♪ But I recognize... ♪</i>

04:55.875 --> 04:57.833
Russo:
<i>I kept saying, "My friend</i>
<i>will be out in a minute</i>

04:57.916 --> 05:00.000
<i>-to talk apartment with you."</i>
-Robin:<i> But meanwhile,</i>

05:00.083 --> 05:02.416
we were both
secretly like thrilled.

05:02.500 --> 05:06.291
<i>♪ Shoorah! Shoorah!</i>
<i>Hey, I can see you coming ♪</i>

05:06.375 --> 05:08.708
So we were getting into it with
each other. Asking questions...

05:08.791 --> 05:10.958
Russo:
<i>Where you from?</i>
<i>And then the question</i>

05:11.041 --> 05:12.333
<i>I asked her that really</i>

05:12.416 --> 05:13.833
sealed the deal was,

05:13.916 --> 05:16.708
"So, what have you done lately
to make your parents unhappy?"

05:19.250 --> 05:21.333
♪ ♪

05:21.416 --> 05:23.083
Robin:
<i>Growing up,</i>

05:23.166 --> 05:24.875
<i>I was just this little tomboy.</i>

05:26.666 --> 05:28.458
<i>And I just felt like</i>

05:28.541 --> 05:31.333
<i>I was always observing life,</i>

05:31.416 --> 05:34.583
<i>and I couldn't picture my life</i>

05:34.666 --> 05:37.083
as a grownup, fitting into

05:37.166 --> 05:39.041
the world that I saw around me.

05:42.500 --> 05:44.041
<i>I couldn't imagine</i>
<i>getting married</i>

05:44.125 --> 05:46.458
<i>and living this life</i>
<i>that my mother lived.</i>

05:49.041 --> 05:51.250
<i>I was always looking</i>
<i>at the clock,</i>

05:51.333 --> 05:53.833
<i>like I was perpetually bored.</i>

05:57.375 --> 05:59.791
<i>And when I finally</i>
<i>did come out,</i>

05:59.875 --> 06:02.583
<i>it was almost as if I was</i>
<i>viewing the world before</i>

06:02.666 --> 06:04.208
<i>in black and white,</i>
<i>and suddenly,</i>

06:04.291 --> 06:05.833
<i>everything burst into color.</i>

06:05.916 --> 06:09.000
♪ ♪

06:14.291 --> 06:16.750
<i>So then, when I met Russo,</i>

06:18.208 --> 06:20.916
it was just like this is
what I've been waiting for.

06:22.208 --> 06:25.291
Me, too. It was
like, oh my god.

06:25.375 --> 06:27.541
And I was--
And then, I had to
go back to New York,

06:27.625 --> 06:30.958
and I was terrified
of losing her.

06:31.041 --> 06:33.458
-This is February and, April?
-April.

06:33.541 --> 06:35.125
I moved to New York.

06:37.666 --> 06:39.375
<i>And all of our friends said,</i>

06:39.458 --> 06:42.750
"What are you doing?
Slow down. You're crazy."

06:42.833 --> 06:45.916
And everyone said,
"You can't do that,"
and, "She's so young."

06:46.000 --> 06:47.375
And we just kept
saying, "No, no,

06:47.458 --> 06:49.083
we love each other.
Leave us alone."

06:51.000 --> 06:52.166
<i>I remember at one point,</i>

06:52.250 --> 06:55.000
<i>we met with Russo's</i>
<i>best friend from law school.</i>

06:55.083 --> 06:58.125
♪ ♪

06:58.208 --> 07:01.583
Cris Arguedas:
<i>Russo invited me to</i>
<i>Windows on the World,</i>

07:01.666 --> 07:04.708
<i>at the top of</i>
<i>the World Trade Center,</i>
<i>to meet Robin.</i>

07:06.041 --> 07:07.875
<i>I had never been to</i>
<i>Windows on the World before.</i>

07:07.958 --> 07:09.250
<i>I don't think Russo had either,</i>

07:09.333 --> 07:12.208
but that's how she wanted
to introduce Robin to me

07:12.291 --> 07:15.083
'cause it was, "This is
the love of my life."

07:16.833 --> 07:18.833
<i>She was crazy for her,</i>

07:18.916 --> 07:21.541
<i>and I liked Robin right away.</i>

07:21.625 --> 07:25.291
<i>She's way quieter,</i>
<i>more serious,</i>

07:25.375 --> 07:26.458
<i>but solid.</i>

07:26.541 --> 07:29.833
<i>I did think</i>
<i>she was young,</i>

07:29.916 --> 07:33.833
<i>but they're clearly gonna</i>
<i>be together for a long time.</i>

07:36.250 --> 07:37.458
(traffic noise)

07:37.541 --> 07:39.166
Robin:
<i>We lived in the West Village.</i>

07:40.458 --> 07:42.375
<i>It was very gay.</i>

07:42.458 --> 07:44.208
<i>We used to hang out at</i>
<i>Bonnie and Clydes,</i>

07:44.291 --> 07:46.375
<i>which was a gay bar</i>
<i>on the bottom,</i>

07:46.458 --> 07:48.458
and a women's restaurant,
like a lesbian restaurant,

07:48.541 --> 07:51.041
<i>on the top.</i>

07:51.125 --> 07:54.250
<i>We hung out at</i>
<i>that lesbian restaurant</i>
<i>for a reason.</i>

07:55.458 --> 07:57.125
<i>Because New York</i>
<i>was kinda ugly</i>

07:57.208 --> 07:59.416
<i>on the streets then</i>
<i>and it was scary.</i>

08:00.625 --> 08:02.541
Russo:
<i>One time, some guy</i>

08:02.625 --> 08:04.500
kept following us
down the block,

08:04.583 --> 08:07.833
and screaming. You know,
"You fucking lezzo!"

08:09.416 --> 08:12.541
Robin:
<i>There was always</i>
<i>the threat of violence.</i>

08:12.625 --> 08:15.000
Reporter:
<i>Bouquets of flowers</i>
<i>and the candles</i>

08:15.083 --> 08:16.541
<i>at the door of the Ramrod bar,</i>

08:16.625 --> 08:18.250
<i>they're really symbols</i>
<i>of the mourning,</i>

08:18.333 --> 08:19.750
<i>a feeling of mourning</i>
<i>for the two dead</i>

08:19.833 --> 08:23.000
<i>and the others who've been</i>
<i>shot down here on West Street.</i>

08:23.083 --> 08:25.583
<i>Many of the people here see</i>
<i>it not just as an attack on</i>

08:25.666 --> 08:27.333
<i>the individuals that</i>
<i>happened to be here,</i>

08:27.416 --> 08:30.041
<i>but as an attack on</i>
<i>the gay community.</i>

08:30.125 --> 08:32.375
I wanna live my life!
I don't wanna be killed

08:32.458 --> 08:34.416
on these streets!
This is ridiculous!

08:34.500 --> 08:36.875
Russo:
<i>Mom would never</i>
<i>hold my hand.</i>

08:36.958 --> 08:38.583
Robin:
<i>I was always terrified</i>
<i>to hold Mom's hand</i>

08:38.666 --> 08:41.083
-on the street or put
my arm around her.
-I'd say, "Come on, we gotta..."

08:41.166 --> 08:43.750
"No, I'm too--
No. It's not worth it.
It's too dangerous."

08:43.833 --> 08:46.041
(crowd chanting)

08:46.125 --> 08:48.041
Cris:
<i>In the gay community,</i>

08:48.125 --> 08:51.291
we were creating
a new world, you know.

08:51.375 --> 08:54.541
We were creating
a world of gay liberation.

08:54.625 --> 08:57.750
<i>And your parents</i>
<i>were part of that.</i>

08:57.833 --> 09:00.375
♪ ♪

09:00.458 --> 09:03.583
<i>Russo and I had such</i>
<i>a close relationship.</i>

09:03.666 --> 09:06.541
<i>We could talk about</i>
<i>anything and did.</i>

09:06.625 --> 09:08.333
<i>I guess she had been</i>
<i>saying to me on the phone.</i>

09:08.416 --> 09:11.666
She's very happy.
She loves Robin.
She's glad she came out.

09:11.750 --> 09:14.291
"But now, I'm never gonna
be able to have children."

09:16.458 --> 09:19.708
<i>And, you know, Russo,</i>
<i>she was worldly,</i>

09:19.791 --> 09:23.416
<i>and she had lived a life,</i>
<i>and she had had two husbands.</i>

09:24.875 --> 09:28.708
<i>She knew a lot more</i>
<i>about herself</i>

09:28.791 --> 09:31.083
<i>and life and politics.</i>

09:32.833 --> 09:35.458
<i>She knew what she wanted.</i>

09:35.541 --> 09:38.000
Russo:
<i>I wanted kids since</i>
<i>I myself was a kid.</i>

09:38.083 --> 09:40.208
<i>I've always wanted kids.</i>

09:41.875 --> 09:44.458
<i>With my second husband,</i>
<i>I tried to get pregnant.</i>

09:44.541 --> 09:48.833
<i>And I was so desperate</i>
<i>to have it work</i>
<i>and have a life.</i>

09:48.916 --> 09:51.833
<i>I was trying for about</i>
<i>two and a half years, and...</i>

09:53.083 --> 09:56.375
<i>couldn't. Didn't.</i>

09:56.458 --> 10:00.000
<i>You know, I also realized</i>
<i>that that was a blessing</i>

10:00.083 --> 10:03.458
<i>because I was a lesbian.</i>

10:03.541 --> 10:05.416
<i>And then when</i>
<i>I finally came out,</i>

10:05.500 --> 10:09.083
it was never on my radar
again that I would have kids.

10:09.166 --> 10:10.750
It was...

10:10.833 --> 10:12.375
Gay couples just
didn't have kids.

10:12.458 --> 10:15.375
♪ ♪

10:15.458 --> 10:17.875
(bar chatter)

10:17.958 --> 10:21.458
Robin:
<i>Coming out, being gay,</i>
<i>meant that you</i>

10:21.541 --> 10:23.291
<i>were not gonna have children.</i>

10:24.666 --> 10:26.416
