10:46.416 --> 10:49.333
pamphlet, you know,
stapled on the sides,

10:49.416 --> 10:52.791
<i>with a pink cover that</i>
<i>said something like,</i>

10:52.875 --> 10:56.041
<i>"We can make our own babies,"</i>
<i>or something like that.</i>

10:56.125 --> 10:58.500
♪ ♪

10:58.583 --> 11:00.083
<i>And so, I bought it,</i>

11:00.166 --> 11:02.666
<i>and when Russo</i>
<i>and Robin came to visit,</i>

11:02.750 --> 11:06.875
I said, "Look. You can.
You can have children."

11:08.041 --> 11:09.458
Russo:
<i>She gave us a little pink</i>

11:09.541 --> 11:12.750
mimeographed thing that
two women had written.

11:12.833 --> 11:15.125
Robin:
<i>It was like homemade</i>
<i>little drawings,</i>

11:15.208 --> 11:18.833
pen and ink, like,
really hokey.

11:20.625 --> 11:21.958
<i>And the pamphlet was like,</i>

11:22.041 --> 11:24.416
<i>"Sarah and Emily are lesbians</i>

11:24.500 --> 11:26.458
<i>who wanna have children."</i>

11:26.541 --> 11:27.875
-Russo:<i> It was how-to!</i>
-Robin:<i> A how-to.</i>

11:27.958 --> 11:31.166
<i>How to artificially</i>
<i>inseminate without a doctor.</i>

11:36.958 --> 11:38.458
Russo:
<i>And when you think about it,</i>

11:38.541 --> 11:41.166
it's so... simple.

11:48.791 --> 11:50.791
Robin:
<i>And it just opened up</i>
<i>this incredible door.</i>

11:50.875 --> 11:53.208
<i>It was like it was</i>
<i>really possible.</i>

11:53.291 --> 11:54.791
<i>We could have children.</i>

11:54.875 --> 11:57.958
♪ ♪

11:59.875 --> 12:01.791
Cris:
<i>So, they were talking about,</i>
<i>"Well, who could it be?</i>

12:01.875 --> 12:03.791
<i>Who could be the donor?"</i>

12:03.875 --> 12:05.416
<i>Who could fill that role?</i>

12:05.500 --> 12:07.958
<i>And that meant who's a,</i>
<i>who's a...</i>

12:08.041 --> 12:11.291
man who's a good guy and has...

12:11.375 --> 12:14.250
good genes and would
be willing to do this

12:14.333 --> 12:16.000
under those terms.

12:16.083 --> 12:20.041
You can't really imagine a
straight man wanting to do that.

12:20.125 --> 12:23.250
(disco music playing)

12:23.333 --> 12:26.291
(inaudible)

12:28.875 --> 12:32.916
We wanted gay men
as donors because...

12:33.000 --> 12:35.666
they were simpatico
with what we were doing.

12:35.750 --> 12:38.833
<i>♪ Baby, show me your love ♪</i>

12:38.916 --> 12:42.416
Russo:
<i>The culture certainly</i>
<i>was pre-HIV.</i>

12:42.500 --> 12:44.500
<i>No one knew about HIV,</i>

12:44.583 --> 12:46.458
<i>and it was a very</i>

12:46.541 --> 12:50.083
wild, loose culture
in the gay community.

12:50.166 --> 12:53.041
♪ ♪

12:57.666 --> 13:01.583
Robin:
<i>And I think for these guys</i>
<i>at the time, it was like,</i>

13:01.666 --> 13:03.791
